The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Seniors golf from today

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: After eleven years, the All India Seniors Golf Championship will be played at the par-72 Royal Calcutta Golf Club from Tuesday. 

The tournament is co-presented by The Telegraph and Eveready Industries and is supported by Pepsi and Kingfisher. 

Around 100 golfers will be taking part in this four-day national ranking event. The tournament would be played in four age categories ?? 50-55 years, 56-60 years, 61-65 years and super seniors (above 65 years). 

The Indian squad for the Asia Pacific Senior Amateur Golf Championship will be selected on the basis of the performance in this meet. 

Defending champion Vikramjit Singh, Ashok Malik, Lakshman Singh and Alan Singh are expected to take part. 

For the first time, the Indian Golf Union has further increased the scope of this event by including a Mid Amateur Golf Championship as part of this championship. 




